&lt;p&gt;I am currently researching topics for my masters thesis, I have done a lot of reading about NeuroEvolution and NEAT in particular and I find these approaches very interesting and would love to incorporate them into my thesis.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The problem lies in that many of these techniques seem to be very simple to parallelize. I&#39;m sure this isn&#39;t a usual complaint, however, in my masters course, High Performance Computing, they have warned us that we should avoid such topics.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I was wondering if anyone could point me towards any literature which would avoid master-slave/embarrassingly parallel techniques and require more involved message passing between computing nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

